
[1]plica

   PLI'CA, n. [L. a fold.] The plica polonica is a disease of the hair,
   peculiar to Poland and the neighboring countries. In this disease, the
   hair of the head is matted or clotted by means of an acrid viscid humor
   which exudes from the hair.
